chief_complaints: removal of calculus and spyglass cholangioscopy
symptoms_narrative: Patient's CD confirms CBD stones and he was transferred to the Johns Hopkins Hospital for ERCP in the setting of altered anatomy.
past_medical_history: Patient has a history of pilgratitude anatomy for PUD from the 1980s, COVID positive in August of 2020, atrial fibrillation, flutter not on anticoagulated drugs, bradycardia status post pacemaker in 2017, CKD 2 baseline nonverbal dementia, PEG dependent, vocal cord paralysis from a thyroidectomy in 1995, admitted for sepsis secondary to multilobar aspiration pneumonia and ascending cholangitis with E coli sepsis.
stone_description: A 20 mm calculus was present in the distal bile duct.
prior_stent_status: Previously placed bile duct stent was in place.
cholangiogram_free_text: Cholangiogram showed no residual stones or filling defects.
impressions: ['Normal upper GI examination', 'Successful removal of calculus from distal bile duct', 'No residual stones or filling defects on cholangiogram']

chief_complaints: evaluation and treatment of abdominal pain of suspected biliary origin
symptoms_narrative: Patient has elevated liver function tests and bilirubin.
major_papilla_free_text: The papilla has a hook nose configuration with a prominent intramural segment.
bile_duct_cannulation_difficulty: Cannulation of the bile duct was performed with ease.
stone_description: A filling defect in the common bile duct consistent with a stone. Gallstones were present within the cystic duct.
plastic_stent_details: 7 Fr x 5 cm double pigtail plastic stent
stent_placement_narrative: The single stent was placed successfully.
impressions: ['Normal EGD examination of esophagus, stomach, duodenum', 'Prominent papilla with hook nose configuration', 'Successful bile duct cannulation', 'Stone extraction from common bile duct', 'Gallstones in cystic duct', 'Placement of 7 Fr x 5 cm double pigtail plastic stent']

chief_complaints: therapy of a pancreatic duct stricture and stone
symptoms_narrative: Patient presents with decreased appetite and abdominal pain but no fever or leukocytosis.
past_medical_history: The patient has a history of metastatic hypothesis and carcinoma, pancreatic duct stricture system, recent acupuncture pancreatitis.
social_history: The patient has had extensive tobacco use, approximately about 100 pack years.
stone_description: Multiple calcified calculi were present in the dorsal pancreatic duct.
pancreatogram_overall: mildly dilated dorsal pancreatic duct with minimal side branch dilation
impressions: ['Normal upper GI examination', 'Normal major and minor papilla', 'Mildly dilated dorsal pancreatic duct with minimal side branch dilation', 'Multiple calcified calculi in the dorsal pancreatic duct', 'Successful electrohydraulic lithotripsy and stone removal']

chief_complaints: treatment of alcoholic chronic obstructive pancreatitis with a mild stone in the head of the pancreas
symptoms_narrative: The patient initially presented with abdominal pain, nausea, and vomiting.
stone_description: A large stone was obstructing the pancreatic duct in the head.
pancreatogram_overall: tortuous and dilated main pancreatic duct with a large intraductal filling defect in the head
impressions: ['Normal upper GI examination', 'Successful pancreatic duct cannulation', 'Tortuous and dilated main pancreatic duct with a large intraductal filling defect in the head', 'Large stone obstructing the pancreatic duct in the head', 'Electrohydraulic lithotripsy performed with medium power', 'Procedure terminated due to carbon dioxide retention and prolonged procedure time']
